North West police say they are talking to local farmers in Coligny trying to find the family of a 12-year-old boy who was killed in the area. JOHANNESBURG - North West police say they are talking to local farmers in Coligny trying to find the family of a 12-year-old boy who was killed in the area.Two men have been arrested and appeared in court on Friday for the murder of the boy.The suspects claim the boy jumped off a bakkie while they were taking him to a police station after finding him trying to steal sunflowers.This incident has angered local residents who demonstrated, looting shops and burning houses.The police s Sabata Mokgwabone says no one has come forward to identify the boy or report him missing. We can confirm that the 12-year-old boy has not yet been identified. We re actually appealing to members of the community to come forward with information that can assist us in finding his relatives. WATCH: Coligny residents demand arrests after child killed(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)